      • deepEquals

        public static boolean deepEquals(@NotNull
                                 @NotNull List<byte[]> a,
                                 @NotNull
                                 @NotNull List<byte[]> b)
        The contract of List.equals(Object) is that a "deep equals" is performed, however the actual "deep equals" depends on the elements being compared. In the case of arrays the default Object.equals(Object) is used.

        This method is a convenience utility to check if two lists of byte[] are "equal"

        Parameters:
        a - The first List of byte[]s
        b - The second List of byte[]s
        Returns:
        true if a and b are the exact same array (determined by ==) OR only if a and b are the same size AND Arrays.equals(byte[], byte[]) returns true for every index matching element from a and b.
